{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846936064,"sessionID":"ses_28746714affeWusB3L5wAdfYdz","part":{"id":"prt_d78b9cdbe001WijhQMFW25B6Jx","messageID":"msg_d78b9b1ba001JShW9g6bxS5rPm","sessionID":"ses_28746714affeWusB3L5wAdfYdz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8057af43411141f0a7cf6c2bd08c6c4e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Types & Configuration (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Define error types (`ValidationError`, `NotFoundError`, `InternalError`, `ServiceUnavailableError`, `ConflictError`)\n20:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n21: - [x] **T1.2**: Define `ErrorResponse` and `SuccessResponse` structs\n22:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go -v`\n23: - [x] **T1.3**: Implement `HandleError` function for HTTP error responses\n24:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go -run TestHandleError -v`\n25: - [x] **T1.4**: Define `DeletionReason` enum constants\n26:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDetermineDeletionReason -v`\n27: - [x] **T1.5**: Define `Config` struct with HTTP server parameters\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go -run TestDefaultConfig -v`\n29: - [x] **T1.6**: Define `LifecycleConfig` struct with TTL/idle timeout settings\n30:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDefaultLifecycleConfig -v`\n31: - [x] **T1.7**: Define constants (SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR, labels, annotations)\n32:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go -run TestGVRConstants -v`\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: Store Implementation (ST-2)\n35: \n36: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `Store` interface with CRUD methods\n37:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -v`\n38: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `MemoryStore` with sync.RWMutex\n39:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -run TestMemoryStore -v`\n40: - [x] **T2.3**: Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` with time-based filtering\n41:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -run TestListExpired -v`\n42: - [x] **T2.4**: Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` with LastActivity filtering\n43:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -run TestListInactive -v`\n44: - [x] **T2.5**: Implement expiration index for efficient cleanup\n45:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -run TestExpirationIndex -v`\n46: \n47: ### Phase 3: Kubernetes Client (ST-3)\n48: \n49: - [x] **T3.1**: Implement `K8sClient` struct with dynamic/client-go clients\n50:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go -run TestNewK8sClient -v`\n51: - [x] **T3.2**: Implement `ClientCache` for token-scoped dynamic clients\n52:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go -run TestClientCache -v`\n53: - [x] **T3.3**: Implement `StartInformers` and `WaitForCacheSync`\n54:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go -run TestInformers -v`\n55: - [x] **T3.4**: Implement `PodLister` accessor\n56:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go -run TestPodLister -v`\n57: - [x] **T3.5**: Implement `Informers` wrapper struct\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go -v`\n59: - [ ] **T3.6**: Fix `TestInformers_WaitForCacheSyncTimeout` test failure\n60:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go -run TestInformers_WaitForCacheSyncTimeout -v`\n61: \n62: ### Phase 4: Lifecycle Manager (ST-4)\n63: \n64: - [x] **T4.1**: Implement `SandboxLifecycleManager` struct\n65:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestNewSandboxLifecycleManager -v`\n66: - [x] **T4.2**: Implement `DeleteSandbox` with K8s resource deletion\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDeleteSandbox_Success -v`\n68: - [x] **T4.3**: Implement `ForceDeleteSandbox` with gracePeriod=0\n69:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestForceDelete -v`\n70: - [x] **T4.4**: Implement `IsExpired` time check\n71:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestIsExpired -v`\n72: - [x] **T4.5**: Implement `IsIdleExpired` with LastActivity check\n73:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestIsIdleExpired -v`\n74: - [x] **T4.6**: Implement `GetSandbox` and `UpdateSandboxStatus`\n75:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestGetSandbox -v`\n76: - [x] **T4.7**: Implement `determineDeletionReason` logic\n77:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDetermineDeletionReason -v`\n78: - [x] **T4.8**: Implement `handleDeleteError` for K8s API errors\n79:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestHandleDeleteError -v`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 5: Garbage Collector (ST-5)\n82: \n83: - [x] **T5.1**: Implement `GarbageCollector` struct with interval/timeout\n84:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v`\n85: - [x] **T5.2**: Implement `runLoop` background ticker loop\n86:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestStartStop -v`\n87: - [x] **T5.3**: Implement `runOnce` batch cleanup logic\n88:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestRunOnce -v`\n89: - [x] **T5.4**: Implement expired sandbox cleanup (MaxDurationReached)\n90:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestRunOnce_Expired -v`\n91: - [x] **T5.5**: Implement idle sandbox cleanup (IdleTimeout)\n92:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestRunOnce_Inactive -v`\n93: - [x] **T5.6**: Implement `GCBatchSize` limit (16 items)\n94:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestRunOnce_Limit -v`\n95: - [x] **T5.7**: Implement concurrent-safe cleanup\n96:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go -run TestConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n97: \n98: ### Phase 6: HTTP Server & Router (ST-6)\n99: \n100: - [x] **T6.1**: Implement `HTTPServer` struct with graceful shutdown\n101:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go -run TestStartStop -v`\n102: - [x] **T6.2**: Implement `NewHTTPServer` and `NewHTTPServerWithClients`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go -run TestNewHTTPServer -v`\n104: - [x] **T6.3**: Implement `RegisterHandler` method\n105:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go -run TestRegisterHandler -v`\n106: - [x] **T6.4**: Implement `Start` with error channel\n107:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestStartStopLifecycle -v`\n108: - [x] **T6.5**: Implement `Stop` with context timeout\n109:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go -run TestStop -v`\n110: - [x] **T6.6**: Implement `GracefulShutdown` signal handler\n111:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go -run TestGracefulShutdown -v`\n112: - [x] **T6.7**: Implement `Router` chi.Router wrapper\n113:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go -v`\n114: \n115: ### Phase 7: Middleware (ST-7)\n116: \n117: - [x] **T7.1**: Implement `RecoveryMiddleware` panic handler\n118:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go -v`\n119: - [x] **T7.2**: Implement `LoggingMiddleware` request logger\n120:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go -v`\n121: - [x] **T7.3**: Implement `CORSMiddleware` with config\n122:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go -v`\n123: - [x] **T7.4**: Verify middleware chain order (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n124:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestMiddlewareChain -v`\n125: \n126: ### Phase 8: Handlers (ST-8)\n127: \n128: - [x] **T8.1**: Implement `DeletionHandler` struct\n129:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go -run TestDeletionHandler_Register -v`\n130: - [x] **T8.2**: Implement DELETE `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}`\n131:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go -run TestDeleteSuccess -v`\n132: - [x] **T8.3**: Implement DELETE `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}`\n133:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go -run TestDeleteCodeInterpreter -v`\n134: - [x] **T8.4**: Implement error response handling (404, 500, 503)\n135:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go -run TestDeleteNotFound -v`\n136: - [ ] **T8.5**: Fix `TestDeletionHandler_DeleteMissingSessionID` test (empty sessionID handling)\n137:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go -run TestDeleteMissingSessionID -v`\n138: - [x] **T8.6**: Implement `HealthHandler` with `/healthz` and `/readyz`\n139:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go -v`\n140: - [x] **T8.7**: Implement `HealthChecker` interface\n141:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go -run TestHealthChecker -v`\n142: \n143: ### Phase 9: Integration Tests (ST-9)\n144: \n145: - [x] **T9.1**: E2E health endpoint test\n146:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestE2EHealthz -v`\n147: - [x] **T9.2**: E2E readiness endpoint test\n148:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestE2EReadyz -v`\n149: - [x] **T9.3**: E2E panic recovery test\n150:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestE2EPanicRecovery -v`\n151: - [x] **T9.4**: Server lifecycle test (Start → Stop)\n152:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go -run TestStartStopLifecycle -v`\n153: \n154: ### Phase 10: Test Failure Fixes (ST-10)\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T10.1**: Fix informers WaitForCacheSync timeout test\n157:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go:56-76`\n158:   - Issue: Context cancelled before informers start should return false\n159: - [ ] **T10.2**: Fix empty sessionID handling in DeletionHandler\n160:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete.go:51-58`\n161:   - Issue: Chi router returns 404 for empty path param, expected 400\n162: \n163: ### Phase 11: Full Test Suite Pass (ST-11)\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T11.1**: All unit tests pass\n166:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n167: - [ ] **T11.2**: Test coverage ≥ 80%\n168:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -cover`\n169: - [ ] **T11.3**: No race conditions detected\n170:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -race`\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Task Dependencies\n175: \n176: ```\n177: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3 → T1.4 → T1.5 → T1.6 → T1.7\n178:         ↓\n179: T2.1 → T2.2 → T2.3 → T2.4 → T2.5\n180:         ↓\n181: T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3 → T3.4 → T3.5 → T3.6\n182:         ↓\n183: T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5 → T4.6 → T4.7 → T4.8\n184:         ↓\n185: T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3 → T5.4 → T5.5 → T5.6 → T5.7\n186:         ↓\n187: T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4 → T6.5 → T6.6 → T6.7\n188:         ↓\n189: T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4\n190:         ↓\n191: T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4 → T8.5 → T8.6 → T8.7\n192:         ↓\n193: T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3 → T9.4\n194:         ↓\n195: T10.1 → T10.2\n196:         ↓\n197: T11.1 → T11.2 → T11.3\n198: ```\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Verification Commands\n203: \n204: | Task | Verification Command |\n205: |------|----------------------|\n206: | All unit tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v` |\n207: | Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out` |\n208: | Race detection | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -race` |\n209: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n210: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n211: \n212: ---\n213: \n214: ## Acceptance Criteria\n215: \n216: - [x] HTTPServer graceful shutdown with context timeout\n217: - [x] K8sClient with dynamic/client-go/informers integration\n218: - [x] MemoryStore with expiration and activity indices\n219: - [x] GarbageCollector background cleanup loop\n220: - [x] SandboxLifecycleManager handles Sandbox + SandboxClaim deletion\n221: - [x] Error classification with structured JSON responses\n222: - [x] DeletionReason enum for tracking cleanup triggers\n223: - [x] ClientCache for multi-tenant token-scoped clients\n224: - [x] Chi router with middleware chain (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n225: - [ ] All tests pass (2 failures pending)\n226: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## Files Modified/Created\n231: \n232: | File | Status | Description |\n233: |------|--------|-------------|\n234: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | ✓ Complete | Error types, interfaces, HandleError |\n235: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ✓ Complete | Constants, GVRs, labels |\n236: | `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` | ✓ Complete | HTTP server configuration |\n237: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | ✓ Complete | SandboxLifecycleManager |\n238: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | ✓ Complete | K8sClient, ClientCache |\n239: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ✓ Complete | MemoryStore implementation |\n240: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ✓ Complete | GarbageCollector |\n241: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | ✓ Complete | Informers wrapper |\n242: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | ✓ Complete | HTTPServer lifecycle |\n243: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | ✓ Complete | Router wrapper |\n244: | `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go` | ✓ Complete | Package documentation |\n245: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete.go` | ✓ Complete | DeletionHandler |\n246: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | ✓ Complete | HealthHandler |\n247: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | ✓ Complete | RecoveryMiddleware |\n248: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | ✓ Complete | LoggingMiddleware |\n249: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | ✓ Complete | CORSMiddleware |\n250: | `pkg/workloadmanager/*_test.go` | ⚠ Partial | 2 test failures pending fix |\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Notes\n255: \n256: - Design completed at Stage ST-3\n257: - Implementation 95% complete\n258: - Remaining: 2 test failures to fix\n259:   - `TestInformers_WaitForCacheSyncTimeout`: informers context cancellation\n260:   - `TestDeletionHandler_DeleteMissingSessionID`: Chi router 404 vs expected 400\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Configuration (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define error types (`ValidationError`, `NotFoundError`, `InternalError`, `ServiceUnavailableError`, `ConflictError`)\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestErrorTypes -v`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846936042,"end":1775846936062}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846936069,"sessionID":"ses_28746714affeWusB3L5wAdfYdz","part":{"id":"prt_d78b9ca1c001wOc3Md5YzclgZM","messageID":"msg_d78b9b1ba001JShW9g6bxS5rPm","sessionID":"ses_28746714affeWusB3L5wAdfYdz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-00143b1b980b4ea2880232a523d6c38d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                          HTTPServer                                  │\n22: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐ │\n23: │  │   Router    │  │ Middleware   │  │         Handlers            │ │\n24: │  │  (chi/v5)   │  │ Recovery     │  │ DeletionHandler             │ │\n25: │  │             │  │ Logging      │  │ HealthHandler               │ │\n26: │  │             │  │ CORS         │  │ HandlerFuncAdapter          │ │\n27: │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘ │\n28: │                               │                                      │\n29: │  ┌────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────┐ │\n30: │  │                    SandboxLifecycleManager                       │ │\n31: │  │  - DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                 │ │\n32: │  │  - ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                            │ │\n33: │  │  - IsExpired(sandbox)                                            │ │\n34: │  │  - IsIdleExpired(sandbox, timeout)                               │ │\n35: │  │  - GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                    │ │\n36: │  │  - UpdateSandboxStatus(ctx, sessionID, status)                  │ │\n37: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n38: │                               │                                      │\n39: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n40: │  │ GarbageCollector │  │   K8sClient  │  │       MemoryStore       ││\n41: │  │ - runLoop()      │  │ dynamicClient│  │ - StoreSandbox()        ││\n42: │  │ - runOnce()      │  │ coreClient   │  │ - GetSandboxBySessionID ││\n43: │  │ - Start/Stop     │  │ podLister    │  │ - UpdateSandbox()       ││\n44: │  │                  │  │ informerFact │  │ - DeleteSandboxBySession││\n45: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │ - ListExpiredSandboxes  ││\n46: │                        ┌──────────────┐  │ - ListInactiveSandboxes ││\n47: │                        │  Informers   │  └─────────────────────────┘│\n48: │                        │ factory      │                              │\n49: │                        │ Start/Wait   │                              │\n50: │                        └──────────────┘                              │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: **Component Responsibilities:**\n55: \n56: | Component | Responsibility |\n57: |-----------|---------------|\n58: | `HTTPServer` | HTTP lifecycle management, graceful shutdown, handler registration |\n59: | `Router` | Chi router wrapper for route registration |\n60: | `Middleware` | Recovery, logging, CORS handling for all requests |\n61: | `Handlers` | HTTP endpoint implementation for sandbox operations |\n62: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Core sandbox lifecycle orchestration (create/delete/status) |\n63: | `GarbageCollector` | Background cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes |\n64: | `K8sClient` | Kubernetes client wrapper with dynamic/client-go/informers |\n65: | `Informers` | SharedInformerFactory for pod watching |\n66: | `MemoryStore` | In-memory session tracking with expiration indices |\n67: | `ClientCache` | Token-scoped dynamic client caching for multi-tenant access |\n68: \n69: ### Dependencies\n70: \n71: | Package | Purpose |\n72: |---------|---------|\n73: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP routing |\n74: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes client |\n75: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Dynamic client for CRD operations |\n76: | `k8s.io/client-go/informers` | SharedInformerFactory for caching |\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | K8s API error handling |\n78: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller utilities |\n79: \n80: ## Data Structures\n81: \n82: ### Core Types\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: type SandboxInfo struct {\n86:     Kind               string              // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter/Sandbox/SandboxClaim\n87:     SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n88:     SandboxNamespace   string              // K8s namespace\n89:     SandboxName        string              // K8s resource name\n90:     Name               string              // Runtime name\n91:     SessionID          string              // Session identifier (primary key)\n92:     CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n93:     ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n94:     Status             string              // Current status\n95:     EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Network entry points\n96:     UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n97:     ServiceAccount     string              // K8s service account\n98:     ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n99:     LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Error Types\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type ValidationError struct {\n107:     Field  string\n108:     Reason string\n109: }\n110: \n111: type NotFoundError struct {\n112:     Resource string\n113:     Name     string\n114: }\n115: \n116: type InternalError struct {\n117:     Err error\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n121:     Dependency string\n122: }\n123: \n124: type ConflictError struct {\n125:     Resource string\n126:     Err      error\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### Configuration Types\n131: \n132: ```go\n133: type Config struct {\n134:     Addr            string        // \":8080\"\n135:     ReadTimeout     time.Duration // 15s\n136:     WriteTimeout    time.Duration // 15s\n137:     IdleTimeout     time.Duration // 60s\n138:     ShutdownTimeout time.Duration // 30s\n139:     EnableHealthz   bool\n140:     EnableReadyz    bool\n141: }\n142: \n143: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n144:     DefaultTTL          time.Duration // 8h\n145:     DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration // 15m\n146:     DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration // 8h\n147:     GCInterval          time.Duration // 2m\n148:     GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration // 2m\n149:     DeletionGracePeriod int64         // 0\n150:     DeletionTimeout     time.Duration // 30s\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Constants and GVR\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: const (\n158:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n159:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n160:     DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n161:     SandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n162:     SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n163:     InformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n164:     GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n165:     GCBatchSize               = 16\n166: )\n167: \n168: var SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n169:     Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n170:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n171:     Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n172: }\n173: \n174: var SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n175:     Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n176:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n177:     Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### Labels and Annotations\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: const (\n185:     LabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n186:     LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n187:     LabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n188:     LabelKeyManagedBy    = \"managed-by\"\n189:     ManagedByValue       = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n190:     \n191:     AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n192:     AnnotationKeyPodName     = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n193: )\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ## API Endpoints\n197: \n198: ### Sandbox Deletion\n199: \n200: | Method | Path | Description |\n201: |--------|------|-------------|\n202: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n203: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n204: \n205: **Request:**\n206: - `sessionId` (path parameter) - Required\n207: - `force` (optional) - Force deletion with gracePeriod=0\n208: - `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional) - Deletion grace period\n209: \n210: **Response (200):**\n211: ```json\n212: {\n213:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n214:     \"status\": \"deleted\"\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: **Response (404):**\n219: ```json\n220: {\n221:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n222:     \"status\": \"not_found\",\n223:     \"message\": \"not found: sandbox/session-123\"\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Health Endpoints\n228: \n229: | Method | Path | Description |\n230: |--------|------|-------------|\n231: | GET | `/healthz` | Basic health check |\n232: | GET | `/readyz` | Readiness check (informers sync) |\n233: \n234: ## Error Handling\n235: \n236: ### Error Classification\n237: \n238: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code |\n239: |------------|-------------|------|\n240: | `ValidationError` | 400 | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n241: | `NotFoundError` | 404 | NOT_FOUND |\n242: | `ServiceUnavailableError` | 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n243: | `ConflictError` | 409 | (via K8s API) |\n244: | `InternalError` | 500 | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n245: \n246: ### HandleError Function\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n250:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n251:     \n252:     var resp ErrorResponse\n253:     var status int\n254:     \n255:     switch e := err.(type) {\n256:     case *ValidationError:\n257:         status = http.StatusBadRequest\n258:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", Message: \"Invalid request parameter\", ...}\n259:     case *NotFoundError:\n260:         status = http.StatusNotFound\n261:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"NOT_FOUND\", Message: e.Error()}\n262:     case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n263:         status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n264:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}\n265:     case *InternalError:\n266:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n267:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n268:     default:\n269:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n270:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n271:     }\n272:     \n273:     w.WriteHeader(status)\n274:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n275: }\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### K8s API Error Handling\n279: \n280: ```go\n281: func handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n282:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n283:         return nil  // Already deleted, success\n284:     }\n285:     if apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n286:         return &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n287:     }\n288:     return &InternalError{Err: err}\n289: }\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ## Testing Strategy\n293: \n294: ### Test Patterns\n295: \n296: 1. **Unit Tests** - Each component tested independently with mocks\n297: 2. **Fake K8s Clients** - `dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient`, `fake.NewSimpleClientset`\n298: 3. **Mock Logger** - Simple struct capturing Info/Error calls\n299: 4. **Test Informer Factory** - `NewTestInformerFactory` for controlled sync\n300: \n301: ### Test Helpers\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type mockLogger struct {\n305:     infoCalls  []string\n306:     errorCalls []string\n307: }\n308: \n309: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n310:     l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n311: }\n312: \n313: func (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {\n314:     l.errorCalls = append(l.errorCalls, msg)\n315: }\n316: \n317: func NewTestInformerFactory(client kubernetes.Interface) informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n318:     return informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, time.Minute)\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Test Coverage Areas\n323: \n324: | File | Test Coverage |\n325: |------|---------------|\n326: | `lifecycle_test.go` | DeleteSandbox, ForceDeleteSandbox, IsExpired, IsIdleExpired, GetSandbox, UpdateSandboxStatus |\n327: | `k8s_client_test.go` | NewK8sClient, StartInformers, WaitForCacheSync, PodLister, ClientCache |\n328: | `store_test.go` | StoreSandbox, GetSandboxBySessionID, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandbox, ListExpired/Inactive |\n329: | `garbage_collector_test.go` | runOnce, Start/Stop, idle timeout behavior |\n330: | `handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | HTTP deletion endpoints, error handling |\n331: | `server_test.go` | Start/Stop, GracefulShutdown, handler registration |\n332: \n333: ### Integration Test Strategy\n334: \n335: ```go\n336: func TestIntegration_ServerLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n337:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n338:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n339:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n340:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n341:     \n342:     k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n343:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n344:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n345:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n346:     }\n347:     \n348:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n349:     logger := &mockLogger{}\n350:     cfg := DefaultConfig()\n351:     \n352:     server := NewHTTPServerWithClients(cfg, logger, k8sClient, store)\n353:     \n354:     // Register handlers, start server, verify endpoints\n355: }\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ## Validation Checklist\n359: \n360: - [x] HTTPServer graceful shutdown with context timeout\n361: - [x] K8sClient with dynamic/client-go/informers integration\n362: - [x] MemoryStore with expiration and activity indices\n363: - [x] GarbageCollector background cleanup loop\n364: - [x] SandboxLifecycleManager handles Sandbox + SandboxClaim deletion\n365: - [x] Error classification with structured JSON responses\n366: - [x] DeletionReason enum for tracking cleanup triggers\n367: - [x] ClientCache for multi-tenant token-scoped clients\n368: - [x] Chi router with middleware chain (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n369: \n370: ## Open Questions\n371: \n372: - Q: Should Store interface support persistent backend (Redis/etcd)?\n373:   - A: MemoryStore is current implementation; Store interface allows future extension\n374: \n375: - Q: Should AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers watch CR status changes?\n376:   - A: Current implementation uses Pod informers; CR informers can be added via client-go generated informers\n377: \n378: - Q: Should GarbageCollector emit metrics for deletion counts/reasons?\n379:   - A: Not implemented yet; can be added via Prometheus integration\n380: \n381: ## References\n382: \n383: - `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` - Generated client-go for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n384: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` - AgentRuntime CRD definition\n385: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` - CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n386: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` - Shared types, labels, annotations, conditions\n387: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n388: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Client-go library documentation\n\n(End of file - total 388 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775846936040,"end":1775846936065}}}}
